<br>
I know these things I am gonna talk about have got to be on your minds, and it's been biting at the back of mine, as well.<br>
<br>
We do have several upper levels that can group together and get exp or what not.  Problem is, we have more than 6 and less than 12 on at any given time.  <br>
<br>
The other day, Whorl and I were talking and dying for some others to come online so we could all group...man were we bored! <br>
<br>
Anyway, a few people came on and we quickly snatched em up, formed a group and went hunting.  This happened yesterday too with trying for Tchallar's Call of Flame quest.  I was online for an hour, got to MM and waited.  I got bored and logged on as Azariel, which I will continue to do at times.  <br>
<br>
Well, Tchallar came on, but still, no healer or anyone else online.  Finally, some of the others came online and we grouped almost immediatly and went to work.<br>
<br>
Here is the problem and I want you to know that it is uncomfortably and makes me sad.  When we get a full group, it is guaranteed that some of the others will get online too...but our group will already be full.<br>
<br>
I just want you to know that I am sorry if this happens and we all can't get together...<br>
<br>
I hate having to tell someone that we are full and got no room.  Please be aware that these things happen.  <br>
<br>
Now for the record, nobody has gotten mad or anything.  I just been thinking about this and it has been buggin me somewhat that we can't all group all the time and I am sorry if one of us gets left out of a group cause of this.<br>
<br>
