<br>
While you end up having to leave some people out, your solution is probably the least disruptive for all concerned.  There is a point however at which two groups of 4 or 5 can at least hunt in close proximity and be able to maintain cross-group communication for things such as buffs or anti-wipeout help.  Two groups hunting the same spawn points or pulls becomes a mini-raid, which is a whole different story.  There is a benefit however in that the two groups can now accomplish something that a single group might not have been able to do.<br>
<br>
